name: litre
description: Litre (1 dm3)

name: centilitre
description: A unit of volume equal to one hundreth of a liter.

name: gram per cubic centimetre
description: g/cm3 as a unit of measure for the density of gas. This is necessary for dangerous substance articles for determination of the quantities that can be stored together on the shelf.

name: gram per square centimetre
description: A measure of weight in terms of gram per square centimetre.

name: kilogram per square metre
description: Unit of measure expressed in kilogram per square metre.

name: Pound per square inch, gauge
description: A unit of measure expressed in pound per square inch

name: metre per minute
description: A measure of speed in terms of metres per minute.

name: megabyte
description: A unit of computer memory equal to 1.048.576 (i.e. 2 power 20) bytes.

name: microfarad
description: One millionth of a farad. A farad is the capacitance of a capacitor between the plates of which a potential of 1 volt is created by a charge of 1 Coulomb.

name: gigahertz
description: Hertz multiplied by 10*9.

name: Bit
description: A unit of information equal to one binary digit.

name: acre
description: Acre (4840 yd2)

name: byte
description: A unit of information stored in a computer, equal to eight bits

name: ampere hour
description: Ampere-hour (3,6kC)

name: year
description: The expression of a year as a measure unit.

name: alcoholic strength by mass
description: Alcoholic strength expressed by mass.

name: alcoholic strength by volume
description: Alcoholic strength expressed by volume.

name: capsule
description: Encaspuled dosage form for pharmaceuticals.

name: Joule per square metre
description: A unit of measure of heat energy expressed in joule per square metre.

name: Credit
description: A unit of count defining the number of entries made to the credit side of an account

name: bar
description: A unit of measure equal to 106 dines per square centimeter.

name: British thermal unit
description: British thermal unit (1,055 kilojoules)

name: call
description: Unit of measure for telephone calls. Code value is C0 (C Zero).

name: ohm centimetre
description: Unit of measure expressed in Ohm centimetre.

name: Kilovolt Ampere Hour
description: A unit of accumulated energy of 1000 volt amperes over a period of one hour.

name: candela
description: Unit of measure of light intensity.

name: Colony forming unit per gram
description: Colony forming units per gram is a unit of measure for micro-organisms, such as bacteria, in a food item. Micro-organisms form colonies that are be counted under determined conditions

name: cubic centimetre
description: A system of units for the measurement of volume based on the cubic centimetre.

name: Square metre kelvin per watt

name: square metre per kilogram
description: Unit of measure expressed in square metre per kilogram.

name: Terawatt hour
description: A unit of measure expressed in terawatt hour

name: Kilogram per square centimetre
description: A unit of measure expressed in kilogram per square centimetre

name: Watt per square metre kelvin
description: Unit of measure of thermal conductance expressed in watt per square metre kelvin.

name: Number of Words
description: A unit of count defining the number of words.

name: day
description: The expression of a day as a measure unit

name: degree
description: Unit of measure of temperature.

name: cubic decimetre
description: Unit of measure expressed in cubic decimetre.

name: Dragée
description: Number of dragées (coated tablets) contained in the item's package as a measurement unit.

name: dozen
description: A unit of measure of 12 or group of 12.

name: Degree day
description: A unit of measure used in meteorology and engineering to measure the demand for heating or cooling over a given period of days.

name: Gigacalorie
description: A unit of heat energy equal to one thousand million calories.

name: Dose

name: Square metre per litre

name: Litre per hour

name: Gigabyte
description: A unit of information equal to 10 E9 bytes.

name: Pixel

name: Megapixel
description: A unit of count equal to 10 E6 (1000000) pixels (picture elements).

name: Dots per inch

name: envelope
description: A unit of measure pertaining to the number of envelopes.

name: Square foot

description: Unit of measure of grams per square metre.

name: gross

name: Piece

name: hectometre

name: hertz

name: hour
description: A unit of measure expressed in square inch

name: inch
description: Inch (25,4 mm)

description: A measure of weight in terms of kilogram per metre.

name: kilometre per hour

description: A measure of weight in terms of kilogram per cubic metre.

name: Pound
description: A unit of measure defining the number of litres per day.

name: microgram

name: millicurie

name: square millimetre
description: A unit to measure a surface equal to one millionth of a quadrate

name: cubic millimetre

name: month
description: The expression of a month as a measure unit.

name: megapascal
description: A unit of measure expressed in Megapascal.

name: Cubic metre per hour
description: A unit of measure defining the number of cubic metres per hour.

name: Metre per second
description: A unit of speed expressed in metres per second.

name: newton
description: The SI unit of force, equal to the force that would give a mass of one kilogram an acceleration of one metre per second.

name: number of international units
description: A unit of count defining the number of international units.

name: ounce
description: Ounce GB, US (28,349523 g)

name: fluid ounce (US)
description: Fluid ounce US (29,5735 cm3)

name: fluid ounce (UK)
description: Fluid ounce UK (28,413 cm3)

name: pascal
description: The SI unit of pressure, equal to one Newton per square metre.

name: pair

name: pint (UK)

name: Mile (statute mile)

name: sheet

name: Unit of activity, predefined
description: A measure pertaining to a predefined activity.

name: vial
description: Small glass container. E.g. for a liquid medicine or perfume.

name: Square yard
description: A unit of measure expressed in square yard

name: page
description: The indication of a page as a measurement unit for invoicing purposes, e.g. fax pages.
